definition.value: The southernmost province (marz) of Armenia. It borders the Vayots Dzor marz to the north, Azerbaijan's Nakhchivan exclave to the west, Azerbaijan proper to the east, and Iran to the south. Its capital is Kapan.

One of the provinces (marz) of Armenia. It is in the north-west of the country, bordering Turkey in the west and Georgia in the north. Its capital is Gyumri. Shirak borders the following marzer: Lori (E) and Aragatsotn (S).

One of the provinces (marz) of Armenia. It lies in the south-east of the country, bordering Azerbaijan in both east and west. Vayots Dzor borders the following marzer: Ararat - northwest; Gegharkunik - north; Syunik - southeast.

One of the 17 provinces of Burundi. Its capital is Mwaro.

A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the northern part of the country. It borders the departments of Cuvette and Sangha, and internationally, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and the Central African Republic. The chief town is Impfondo.

A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the central part of the country. It borders the departments of Cuvette, L3koumou, and Pool, and internationally, the Democratic Republic of the Congo on the east and Gabon on the west. The regional capital is Djambala.

A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the southeastern part of the country. It borders the departments of Bouenza, Lekoumou, and Plateaux, and internationally, the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It also surrounds the commune district of the national capital, Brazzaville. The regional capital is Kinkala.
List following additional Districts: Madzia, Kibouende, Kinkembo, Loulombo, Kibossi, Linzolo. These are not so listed by Statoids.
A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the southern part of the country. It borders the departments of Bouenza, Niari, Plateaux, and Pool, and the nation of Gabon. The regional capital is Sibiti.
A Region of the Republic of Congo. The capital is Owando.
A Region of the Republic of Congo.

A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the northern part of the country. It borders the departments of Cuvette, Cuvette-Ouest, and Likouala, and internationally, Cameroon, Gabon and the Central African Republic. The regional capital is Ouesso.
One of the six districts of Cyprus. Part of the British overseas territory of Akrotiri and Dhekelia forms an enclave on the Akrotiri peninsula, under the sovereignty of the United Kingdom.

One of the six districts of Cyprus. Most of the district has been under Turkish control since the 1974 invasion. Since then, the northeastern section, including the Karpasia Peninsula, has been administered separately as the Iskele District, a division not recognized by the Republic of Cyprus.
One of the six districts of Cyprus and it is situated in the western part of Cyprus.

One of the six districts of Cyprus. Its main town is the island country's capital city, Nicosia. The Turkish-occupied northern part of the city is the capital of the so called Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus.
One of the six districts of Cyprus. The authorities in Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus administer the Turkish-occupied parts of Larnaca District as part of Nicosia District.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint John to the north, Saint Joseph to the south, and Saint Andrew to the east.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint George (to the north), Saint Mark (to the south), and Saint Patrick (to the east).
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Luke (to the north) and Saint Patrick (to the east).
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Andrew to the east, and Saint Peter and the Espagnole River to the south.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Paul and part of the Boeri River (to the north), Saint Patrick (to the west), and Saint Luke (to the south).
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Peter to the north, Saint Andrew to the northeast, Saint David to the east, and Saint Joseph to the south.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Andrew to the north; Saint Joseph, Saint Paul and Saint George to the west; and Saint Patrick to the south.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint Joseph to the north, Saint David to the east, and Saint George to the south.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint George, Saint Luke and Saint Mark to the west, and Saint David to the north.
One of Dominica's 10 administrative parishes. It is bordered by Saint John and Saint Peter (to the east), Saint Joseph (to the southwest), and Saint David (to the southeast).

The largest province of Indonesia, comprising a majority part of the western half of the island of New Guinea and nearby islands (see also Western New Guinea). The province originally covered the entire western half of New Guinea, but in 2003, the western portion of the province, on the Bird's Head Peninsula, was declared by the Indonesian Government as a separate province named West Papua.
One of the governorates of Iraq. It is in the east of the country.
A province in the central region of Iraq comprised of 3 districts.
A governorate of Iraq, within the Iraqi Kurdistan Region. Its capital is a city of the same name, As Sulaymaniyah.
A governorate in Iraq, north of Baghdad. Before 1976 the governorate was part of Baghdad Governorate.
